{
  "texts": [
    "We have also curated 16 multi-fidelity datasets based on historical Astra-Zeneca (AZ) HTS data (Supplementary Table 2), the emphasis now being put on expanding the number of compounds in the primary (1 million+) and confirmatory screens (1000 to 10,000).",
    "The search, selection, and filtering steps, along with the naming convention are detailed in Supplementary Notes 5 and 29.",
    "As the QMugs dataset contains a few erroneous calculations, we apply a filtering protocol similar to the drug discovery data and remove the values that diverge by more than 5 standard deviations, which removes just over 1% of the molecules present.",
    "The QMugs properties are listed in Supplementary Table 3.",
    "For the transductive setting, we selected a diverse and challenging set of 10K QMugs molecules (Supplementary Notes 5.1), which resembles the drug discovery setting."
  ]
}